The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	New Delhi: The Football Players Association of India (FPAI), the brainchild of national captain Bhaichung Bhutia, has been granted official membership of the Federation of International Professional Football Players Associations (FIFPro). Chief executive officer Sumit Mukherjee signed the certificate of membership on behalf of FPAI after it became one of two new members introduced at FIFPros general assembly, in Budapest recently.        
	Amsterdam: Belgium coach Dick Advocaat has taken over at Dutch champions AZ Alkmaar following last weeks sacking of Ronald Koeman, the club said Tuesday.        
	Mumbai: Egyptian Ramy Ashour beat Amr Shabana 11-9, 13-15, 11-8, 11-2 in the semi-final of the PSA World Tour Super Series squash Wednesday. Ashour will face Englands Nick Mathew in the final.           
	Khanty Mansiysk: Ruslan Ponomariov of Ukraine defeated Russias Vladimir Malakhov in the rapid tie-break games to enter the World Chess Cup finals where he will meet Boris Gelfand of Israel.         
	Chennai: WGM S. Meenakshi of Indian Airlines beat Soumya Swaminathan in an eighth round match of the 36th National Womens Premier Chess Championship to stay in the lead.        
	Calcutta: Bengal scored 151 for six in their first innings on Day II of their under-16 Vijay Merchant Trophy (East Zone) match in Siliguri on Wednesday.    
	Brief scores    
	Jharkhand 235 (Virat Singh 73; Mithilesh Das 4/41). Bengal 151/6 (A. Raman 44; Ronit Singh 4/32). Match to continue        
	Calcutta: The India U-19 team will play a tri-series in South Africa, prior to the World Cup in New Zealand in January next year.         
	Melbourne: Pakistan pacer Sohail Tanvir Wednesday replaced Sri Lanka off-spinner Muttiah Muralidharan as one of the two foreign recruits in the Australian state side Victoria Bushrangers for the upcoming KFC T20 Big Bash.          
	Karachi: The PCB has roped in former Test skipper Waqar Younis as bowling and fielding coach of the national team for their tour of Australia this month.          
	Karachi: The PCB has requested the ICC special task force for matches against India and a World XI at neutral venues so that it can raise funds.     
